This paper deals with the automatic synthesis of fair non-repudiation protocols, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of logic and formal methods to specify and verify the protocols, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of graph games to compute the solution to assume-guarantee synthesis, which is a topic related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the failure of weak co-synthesis and classical co-synthesis, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a new fair non-repudiation protocol, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
